attribute.description:
Sets the padding mode: 

- Repeat (default) just copies a single element (the first or last element, depending on the align attribute) over and over,
until the desired length has been reached (e.g.: ABCDDDDDD...); 

- Loop copies the whole llll (or a portion of it, depending on the loopsize attribute) over and over, until the desired length
has been reached. Last copy can of course be trimmed, if it overflows the desired length (e.g.: ABCDABCDABCDABCD...); 

- Palindrome Loop is like the previous one, but reverses the loop direction at each new loop (e.g.: ABCDDCBAABCDDCBA...); 

- Palindrome Loop No Repetitions is like the previous one, but avoids repetitions at the loop beginning or end (e.g.: ABCDCBABCDCBA...).

Sets the rounding direction for the specific situation where the align attribute is set to "Center" and an odd number of elements should be split into right and left padding.
- If roundalign is 0 = Left (default), one more element is given at the right padding side;
- If roundalign is 1 = Right, one more element is given at the left padding side.
